The paper deals with algorithms for processing streams of data and estimating statistical quantities with limited memory, which are common topics in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The focus on quantile estimation also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and statistics (cs.ST). The use of frugal algorithms, which are designed to work with small amounts of memory, is a topic that falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT).
